The paper discusses the use of privileged information in improving the accuracy and resilience of detection systems in various security domains. This involves adapting and extending recent advances in knowledge transfer, model influence, and distillation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses face recognition, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
